msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 39"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "39. Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on fine foods"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.39.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.341"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa824"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya "
"viññāpetvā bhuñjanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six ate fine foods after asking for "
"them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics eat fine foods after asking for them?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti."
msgstr "Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t want tasty food?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.88"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa825"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six eat fine foods after asking for "
"them for themselves?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you eat fine foods after asking for them for yourselves?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa826"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for himself—that is,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi."
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, sugar, fish, meat, milk, and curd—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa827"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.39.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa828"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti."
msgstr "At one time a number of monks were sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks who were looking after them asked,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.342"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“We hope you’re bearing up; we hope you’re getting better?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjāma, "
"tena no phāsu hoti;"
msgstr ""
"“Previously we ate fine foods after asking for them, and then we were "
"comfortable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.5"
msgid ""
"idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na viññāpema, tena no na "
"phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But now that this has been prohibited by the Master, we don’t ask because we’"
"re afraid of wrongdoing. And because of that we’re not comfortable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.8"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya "
"viññāpetvā bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat fine foods after asking for them for "
"himself."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.9a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa829"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: seyyathidaṃ → seyyathīdaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who is not sick asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for "
"himself—that is,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi."
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, sugar, fish, meat, milk, and curd—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.12"
msgid ""
"Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā "
"bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "(<em>39</em>:<strong>88</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.39.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.39.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa830"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanānī</strong>ti <strong>sappi nāma"
msgstr "These kinds of fine foods:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "sappi nāma"
msgstr "Ghee:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid ""
"gosappi vā ajikāsappi vā mahiṃsasappi vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati tesaṃ sappi."
msgstr ""
"ghee from cows, ghee from goats, ghee from buffaloes, or ghee from whatever "
"animal whose meat is allowable."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa831"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Navanītaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Butter:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "tesaññeva navanītaṃ."
msgstr "butter from those same animals."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa832"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Telaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Oil:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "tilatelaṃ sāsapatelaṃ madhukatelaṃ eraṇḍatelaṃ vasātelaṃ."
msgstr ""
"sesame oil, mustard seed oil, honey tree oil, castor oil, oil from tallow."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa833"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Madhu nāma"
msgstr "Honey:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "makkhikāmadhu."
msgstr "honey from bees."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa834"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Phāṇitaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Sugar:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "ucchumhā nibbattaṃ."
msgstr "from sugar cane."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa835"></a>
#. VAR: udako → udakacaro (s1-3, pts1, mr)
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Maccho nāma"
msgstr "Fish:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. Here I follow the alternative reading <i lang="pli">udakacaro</i> found in the PTS version. MS has <i lang="pli">udako</i>, which must be an editing mistake.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "udako vuccati."
msgstr "what lives in water is what is meant."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa836"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Maṃsaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Meat:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "the meat of those animals whose meat is allowable."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa837"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "Khīraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Milk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid ""
"gokhīraṃ vā ajikākhīraṃ vā mahiṃsakhīraṃ vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ "
"khīraṃ."
msgstr ""
"milk from cows, milk from goats, milk from buffaloes, or milk from whatever "
"animal whose meat is allowable."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa838"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "Dadhi nāma"
msgstr "Curd:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "tesaññeva dadhi."
msgstr "curd from those same animals."

#. </span>
#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.89"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.343"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa839"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.23"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.24"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa840"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.25"
msgid "Evarūpāni paṇītabhojanānīti"
msgstr "Any of these kinds of fine foods:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.26"
msgid "tathārūpāni paṇītabhojanāni."
msgstr "such kinds of fine foods."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa841"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.27"
msgid "Agilāno nāma"
msgstr "Not sick:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.28"
msgid "yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni phāsu hoti."
msgstr "one who is comfortable without fine foods."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa842"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.29"
msgid "Gilāno nāma"
msgstr "Sick:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.30"
msgid "yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "one who is not comfortable without fine foods."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa843"></a>
#. VAR: viññāpeti, payoge → payoge payoge (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.31"
msgid "Agilāno attano atthāya viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, then for the act of asking for himself, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.32"
msgid "Paṭilābhena “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"When he receives it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.1.33"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.39.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa844"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Agilāno agilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, and he does not perceive himself as sick, and he eats "
"fine foods after asking for them for himself, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Agilāno vematiko paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he eats fine foods after "
"asking for them for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Agilāno gilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he eats fine foods "
"after asking for them for himself, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa845"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is sick, but he does not perceive himself as sick, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Gilāno vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is sick, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Gilāno gilānasaññī anāpatti."
msgstr "If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.39.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa846"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "gilānassa,"
msgstr "if he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "gilāno hutvā viññāpetvā agilāno bhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if he asked for it when he was sick, but eats it when he is no longer sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "gilānassa sesakaṃ bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the leftovers from one who is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "attano,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa847"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc39:pts-cs3.3.11"
msgid "Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on fine foods, is finished."

